<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF9EEF5DFF42FC3FFC74FA5C" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FC3FFE6CFC55" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FC3FFEE7FC1C" bold="true" box="[199,338,906,932]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Comments:</emphasis>
The position of the genus within the 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9EEF5DFC86FC3FFC0CFC1C" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[771,953,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
is still unclear (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF9EEF5DFBF7FC3FFAE8FC1C" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[1138,1373,906,932]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFB58FC3EFAADFC1C" box="[1245,1304,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). The species appears not to be broadly distributed within South American forests, considering its northernmost record (
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF9EEF5DFF1AFC67FECCFC54" box="[159,377,978,1004]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Minas Gerais State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9EEF5DFE01FC67FE78FC55" box="[388,461,978,1005]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FC43FB23FB8C" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FC43FEEEFBA8" bold="true" box="[199,347,1014,1040]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF9EEF5DFEEEFC43FE74FBA8" box="[363,449,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1454,1478]" captionTargetBox="[161,1432,768,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-197@52.[151,1436,758,1389]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 27. Enthephippion olivaceum (Phaneropterinae) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A and B: male and female, respectively; G: sonogram of a sequence of echemes; H: sonogram of one echeme; I: spectrogram of one syllable." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550127" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550127/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
): Males produce sequences of echemes, each one composed by four to seven echemes. Each echeme is composed by 25 to 35 syllables that are produced with increasing intensity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FB8AFD8AFBE0" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" box="[199,575,1086,1113]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FB8AFE1EFBE0" box="[199,427,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 16 ± 2 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FBD7FE6EFBC4" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" box="[199,475,1122,1149]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FBD7FEF5FBC4" box="[199,320,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 7 ± 1.7 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FB32FCBEFB19" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" box="[199,779,1158,1185]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FB32FE9BFB18" box="[199,302,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Duration</emphasis>
: Syllable: 4 ± 0.8 ms; Echeme: 40 ± 6 ms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF42FB1EFCFCFB7D" blockId="54.[151,1437,797,1221]" box="[199,841,1194,1221]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF42FB1EFEEAFB7C" box="[199,351,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 12 ± 1 ms; Echeme: 1.9 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF9EEF5DFD7AFB1FFCF1FB7D" box="[767,836,1194,1221]" degrees="0.14" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" precision="555" value="-0.14">0.14 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF12FAA3FD45FA88" blockId="54.[151,752,1302,1328]" box="[151,752,1302,1328]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF9EEF5DFF12FAA3FD45FA88" bold="true" box="[151,752,1302,1328]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
4. 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9EEF5DFF30FAA3FD45FA88" authority="BURMEISTER, 1838" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[181,752,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">PSEUDOPHYLLINAE BURMEISTER, 1838</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF9EEF5DFF12FAEBFC74FA5C" blockId="54.[151,1436,1374,1508]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
This subfamily is distributed in most of biogeographical regions, except most of the Palearctic Region and North and South Poles. The subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9EEF5DFD87FA37FD0EFA24" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[514,699,1410,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pseudophyllinae">Pseudophyllinae</taxonomicName>
encompasses a thousand species distributed in 246 genera and 19 tribes. Current records point to the occurrence of 148 species of 62 genera within 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF9EEF5DFBB2FA13FBCAFA78" box="[1079,1151,1446,1472]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Here we present records for three tribes of this subfamily, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9EEF5DFD88FA7FFD2CFA5C" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[525,665,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cocconotini">Cocconotini</taxonomicName>
, Plemiinini and 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF9EEF5DFCCBFA7FFC08FA5C" authorityName="Beier" authorityYear="1960" box="[846,957,1482,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Teleutiini">Teleutiini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
